    "description":  "Stateless protocol bridge that connects AI agents to the Planton cloud platform via gRPC (TLS on :443). Exposes 100 MCP tools spanning the full Planton product surface across 17 cloud providers and 362 resource kinds.\nTool categories: - Cloud Resource Lifecycle: create, update, delete, destroy, lock/unlock,\n  and extract env vars for any of the 362 supported kinds\n  (AWS, GCP, Azure, Kubernetes, AliCloud, DigitalOcean, Civo, Cloudflare,\n  Confluent, Auth0, OpenFGA, Snowflake, MongoDB Atlas, Hetzner Cloud,\n  OCI, OpenStack, Scaleway)\n- Stack Jobs: observe provisioning outcomes, retry failures, cancel or\n  approve running jobs, pre-validate prerequisites\n- InfraChart Templates: browse and preview reusable infrastructure chart\n  templates\n- InfraProject Lifecycle: create and manage infrastructure projects sourced\n  from charts or Git repositories\n- InfraPipeline Monitoring & Control: track deployment pipelines, trigger\n  runs, resolve manual gates\n- Dependency Graph: explore resource topology, trace dependencies and\n  dependents, analyze blast radius\n- Config Manager: manage plaintext variables and encrypted secrets with\n  full version history\n- Audit & Version History: paginated change history and unified diffs for\n  any platform resource\n- Context Discovery: list organizations and environments - Presets & Catalog: find pre-configured templates and browse deployable\n  component types with their IaC modules\n- Service Lifecycle: search, create, update, and delete services; manage\n  Git webhook connections\n- Service CI/CD Pipelines: observe build-and-deploy runs, trigger and\n  cancel pipelines, resolve manual gates, read and write pipeline YAML\n- Service Variable Groups: manage named collections of plaintext\n  environment variables; upsert/delete individual entries; resolve and\n  batch-transform $variables-group/ references\n- Service Secrets Groups: manage named collections of encrypted secrets;\n  upsert/delete individual entries; resolve and batch-transform\n  $secrets-group/ references\n- DNS Domains: register and manage custom domain names for service ingress - Tekton Pipelines & Tasks: manage reusable Tekton pipeline and task step\n  templates referenced by services\n\nTwo read-only MCP resources support schema-aware tool calls: - cloud-resource-kinds://catalog — all 362 supported kinds grouped by\n  cloud provider\n- cloud-resource-schema://{kind} — full JSON schema for a specific kind\n  including field types, validation rules, and defaults\n\nEvery tool call opens a short-lived gRPC connection to the Planton backend, executes the RPC, and returns the result. No state is persisted locally.\n",
